properties.headline: Flood Advisory issued February 4 at 9:07PM CST until February 5 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Omaha has issued a

* Flood Advisory for...
An Ice Jam in...
North central Dodge County in east central Nebraska...

* Until 900 PM CST Wednesday.

* At 905 PM CST, an ice jam likely remained in place on the Elkhorn
River between Scribner and West Point. Earlier in the day it was
noted that the ice jam and water levels had increased compared to
Monday. The jam extends from near the bend in the river at Powder
Horn State Wildlife Management area upstream to around Crowell.
Emergency management is monitoring the situation.

* Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Rural Scribner, Powder Horn State Wildlife Management Area, Dead
Timber State Recreation Area, and County Road C.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Advisory means river or stream flows are elevated, or ponding
of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
